description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking to recruit an Advanced Practitioner Band 7 Respiratory Physiotherapist to join the Respiratory Physiotherapy Team at Northern Devon Healthcare Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be a part of shaping new services within the respiratory physiotherapy team at the Trust. The successful candidate will work with the Respiratory Advanced practitioner (B8), Respiratory Consultants and Wider MDT to help redesign respiratory outpatient services. The work will include working with patients with breathing pattern disorders and those with long term neuromuscular conditions. The post holder will support the specialist respiratory physiotherapists, occupational therapists and community therapists in developing knowledge and skills with regards to managing these patient groups, and will also act as the trust lead for Suction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate an extensive range of specialist knowledge, experience and expertise in the field of respiratory physiotherapy. You will have had experience at a senior level including acute medicine, and the care of those with chronic respiratory disease. As part of your role in ensuring excellence you will initiate and participate in evidence-based projects and audit, to improve both immediate and future quality of patient care. A strong commitment to training at undergraduate and post-graduate levels is essential and an interest in research is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be flexible, highly motivated and committed towards team working, with excellent communication, problem-solving and organisational skills. You will have proven experience and skills in leadership and supervision. In return you can expect to be supported in your professional development to enhance skills appropriate to the needs of the service and client group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours available for this post are 22.5 per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 11/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
